The paper deals with a secure communication network using directional modulation, which involves optimization of power allocation, beamforming vector, and artificial noise projection matrices. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also addresses the issue of security and interference, which is related to computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of a UAV user and control center also involves system control and optimization (cs.SY). Finally, the optimization problem is solved using an iterative algorithm, which involves artificial intelligence and optimization techniques (cs.AI).
